text: Bolshiye Karkaly () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Bolshekarkalinksy Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 488 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Bolshiye Karkaly
